{"ts":"2026-07-15T20:00:19.764Z","author":"codex-audit-20260715","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"Live reproduction on current main with only project packages: pm package doctor --project --isolated --detail deep --trace --json returns warning status for pm-changelog renderers json and toon. The package callback is well-behaved and returns null for every non-marker result, so output is not corrupted; however doctor sees only global registration and cannot prove ownership. Closed pm-5teq correctly introduced warnings for dangerous global overrides and must not be reversed. Open pm-ixoa covers an actual calendar and guide-shell service collision. This item adds positive scoping metadata so safe package renderers can be both explicit and warning-free."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-nf7q"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Scoped renderer ownership: safe package renderers should not keep isolated package doctor in warning state"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Add command or result ownership metadata for extension renderers so doctor can distinguish globally corrupting overrides from safe null-fallback renderers used only by their package commands."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","diagnostics","extensions","packages","renderers"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-15T20:00:19.764Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-15T20:00:19.764Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"codex-audit-20260715"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":180},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"The renderer registration contract can declare command paths or a result discriminator without breaking existing callbacks; doctor warns for unscoped or provably unsafe global overrides but treats declared safe ownership as healthy; pm-changelog JSON and TOON marker renderers are migrated to the scoped contract and isolated deep doctor is warning-free; unrelated commands still fall back to native rendering; collisions between packages remain visible; SDK types, define or compose helpers, scaffold, package-author docs, describe output, runtime contracts, and focused real-CLI plus SDK-harness tests are updated together"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-15T20:00:19.764Z","author":"codex-audit-20260715","text":"Duplicate check evidence: all-status searches for pm-changelog renderer warning scoped renderer command ownership and doctor false positive found only closed pm-5teq diagnostics and the distinct open pm-ixoa service collision."}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"b3e7e19aade217b6ee7b46d656333cda0f849dc42c8f1c88039926f3140c352c","message":""}
